President Barack Obama has announced his intent to nominate several individuals for key administration posts. These include Susan Beard as Inspector General for the Department of Energy, Susan S. Gibson as Inspector General for the National Reconnaissance Office, Mary Beth Leonard as Representative of the United States of America to the African Union, with the rank of Ambassador for the Department of State, and Lawrence Robert Silverman as Ambassador to the State of Kuwait for the Department of State. President Obama also announced his intent to appoint Rosemary Freitas Williams as Assistant Secretary for Public and Intergovernmental Affairs for the Department of Veterans Affairs, Jordan Goodman and Howard Konar as members of the United States Holocaust Memorial Council. President Obama expressed confidence in these individuals and their ability to tackle the challenges facing America.